[ 1 ] WHY OOPS EXISTS  ( VERY IMPORTANT)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BEFORE WRITING A SINGLE CLASS, YOU MUST UNDERSTAND WHY OOPS WAS CREATED.

  • LIMITATIONS OF PROCEDURAL PROGRAMMING
  • CODE DUPLICATION PROBLEMS
  • DIFFICULTY IN MAINTENANCE & SCALING
  • REAL-WORLD PROBLEM MODELING
  • REUSABILITY OF CODE
  • MAINTAINABILITY & READABILITY
  • SCALABILITY FOR LARGE SYSTEMS
  • PROCEDURAL VS OOPS THINKING
  • HOW OOPS SOLVES REAL SOFTWARE PROBLEMS

IF THIS IS WEAK, OOPS WILL FEEL CONFUSING LATER.


